When South African Minister of Police Fikile Mbalula tweeted a message wishing his Twitter followers a safe and happy Christmas on December 25, many of them noticed that the message had apparently been sent from Dubai.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

The information on the tweet's origins had been captured in its geotag, which is an electronic tag that assigns a geographical location to a photograph or video, or, in this case, a posting on a social media website.
